Quote:  For impatient young men, anxious to be `in the first of the rush', and for those weakened by privation, every West Coast river was a likely grave. <i>Ibid.</i> 528 `THE FIRST OF THE RUSH': the phrase is self-explanatory. Some deference was due to those `in the first of the rush'.
